A PHP array is in fact just an ordered hash-map (IE.. hash map with an associated linked list which tracks the iteration order).<p>When you do an array append, the logic PHP runs is it tries to guess what the most logical key would be, add that to the hash-map and then to the end of the linked list.<p><pre><code>  $a = array();
  $a[] = 'A';
  $a[] = 'B';
  print_r($a);

  Array
  (
      [0] => A
      [1] => B
  )

  $b = array();
  $b[5] = 'A';
  $b[100] = 'B';
  $b[] = 'C';
  print_r($b);

  Array
  (
      [5] => A
      [100] => B
      [101] => C
  )</code></pre>
